div.p:
The Oification begins in this Bone at two Points, between the Laminae of this Bone there's a Cavity call'd Sinus Frontalis; 1. Os Frontis. it's oft-times double, which by two mall Foramina enter into the Notrils; this Sinus makes the inide of this Bone arie in a ridge, which begins about the top of the Forehead, where the Hair grows not, and reaches to the Crita Galli; for which reaon we mut not Trepan here, let we offend the Dura Mater on each ide the ridge, whenas the middle is not perforated by much; the upper Lamina of this coming to the Eyes, where
turning inwards, makes up part of the Orbit on the upper ide: This: Sinus is lined with a thick Membrane full of Glands, which eparate a Mucus to moiten the Noe; in Brutes it's very large, but not o in Men; yet once I aw a Skull which had it extreamly large, and divided in four or five Cells, quite round the Bais of the Os Frontis, o that the Internal Protuberances almot hid the Crita Galli;
yet ometimes this Sinus is quite obliterated, and the Membrane turn'd bony, as the Oific Liquor increaes, and we incline in Age.



This in all Creatures is only moveable,
except as ome affirm in the Crocodile,
who moves the upper only.

We will begin with the Superior;
but firt I mut inform you, that ince
both Extremities are double, I hall
only peak of them in the ingular number,
for by demontrating one ide,
you at the ame time hew the other.
